      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(reply): mirror same-channel Slack final replies",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Mirror same-surface external final replies into the owning session transcript after dispatcher delivery succeeds.\n- Treat dispatcher post-hook capture as canonical: rewritten finals persist rewritten content, observed-empty finals persist nothing, and unobserved finals keep the pre-hook fallback.\n- Add regression coverage for Slack same-channel delivery, delivery-hook rewrites, and delivery-hook content removal.\n\n## Issue\nFixes #92489\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: Slack channel/thread turns where `Provider` already matches `OriginatingChannel` should persist delivered assistant final replies to the owning session transcript, even though they do not use the routed-reply path. Delivery hooks must remain authoritative so redacted or stripped payloads are not restored into durable transcript state.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout at PR head `9751122cb014a370629216a6c0ea483156b53385` on macOS, Node v24.15.0, running the real `dispatchReplyFromConfig` test harness for Slack same-channel dispatch.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts --testNamePattern 'same-channel Slack final replies'`\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output): Copied terminal output from the focused run:\n\n```text\nRUN  v4.1.7 /Users/andy/openclaw-92489\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed | 201 skipped (204)\nDuration  2.97s\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The same-channel Slack final reply path appends normal delivered replies to `agent:main:slack:channel:C123`; dispatcher-hook rewrites append the rewritten text; dispatcher-hook stripped finals do not append the original pre-hook text.\n- What was not tested: A live Slack workspace/API end-to-end run was not performed in this environment.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: The proof uses the repository's dispatch-layer Slack harness to exercise the exact same-channel path without external Slack credentials. Live Slack delivery plus transcript readback is still the strongest external proof.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Before this patch, same-channel Slack finals could be delivered without appending an assistant transcript entry; the first implementation also risked falling back to pre-hook content when a hook stripped all sendable parts.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts --testNamePattern 'same-channel Slack final replies'` - 3 tests passed, 201 skipped.\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts` - 204 tests passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts` - passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --write src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts && git diff --check` - passed.\n- `pnpm tsgo:prod` - passed.\n- `pnpm run test:extensions:package-boundary:compile` - passed; 114 plugins compiled.\n",
        "branch": "codex/92489-slack-transcript-mirror",
